cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper deals with improving the performance of semantic segmentation of aerial images using neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes two attention-based modules to enhance the feature representation, which involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Additionally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for feature extraction, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with the spatial distribution of features, which can be related to the field of graphics (cs.GR).
